# Environment Variables Configuration

## Required for External API Integration

### Copy this file to .env and add your API keys

# RapidAPI Configuration (Job Search)
# Get your key from: https://rapidapi.com/
# Subscribe to JSearch API: https://rapidapi.com/letscrape-6bRBa3QguO5/api/jsearch
RAPIDAPI_KEY=your_rapidapi_key_here

# OpenAI API Configuration (Enhanced Chatbot) - OPTIONAL
# Get your key from: https://platform.openai.com/
# Leave empty to use rule-based chatbot
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Affinda API Configuration (Resume Parser) - OPTIONAL
# Get your token from: https://www.affinda.com/
# Leave empty to use built-in resume parser
AFFINDA_API_TOKEN=

## Instructions

### 1. RapidAPI (Job Search) - Free Tier Available
```
1. Go to https://rapidapi.com/
2. Sign up with Google/GitHub/Email
3. Search for "JSearch" in API marketplace
4. Click "Subscribe to Test"
5. Select "Basic" (Free - 5,000 requests/month)
6. Copy your API key
7. Paste it above as: RAPIDAPI_KEY=your_actual_key
```

### 2. OpenAI API (Optional - Enhanced Chatbot)
```
1. Go to https://platform.openai.com/
2. Sign up and add payment method (required)
3. Go to "API Keys" in left sidebar
4. Click "Create new secret key"
5. Copy the key (starts with 'sk-')
6. Paste it above as: OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your_actual_key

Note: If not configured, app will use built-in rule-based chatbot
```

### 3. Affinda API (Optional - Resume Parser)
```
1. Go to https://www.affinda.com/
2. Sign up for free account
3. Navigate to Dashboard → API Keys
4. Copy your API token
5. Paste it above as: AFFINDA_API_TOKEN=your_actual_token

Note: If not configured, app will use built-in resume parser
```

## Usage

### Option 1: Using .env file (Recommended for local development)
```bash
# Copy this file
cp .env.example .env

# Edit .env with your actual keys
# Then start the application - Spring Boot will read from environment
```

### Option 2: Using application.properties
```bash
# Edit backend/src/main/resources/application.properties
# Replace the placeholders:
rapidapi.key=your_actual_key_here
openai.api.key=sk-your_actual_key_here
affinda.api.token=your_actual_token_here
```

### Option 3: Using environment variables (Production)
```bash
# Set environment variables before starting
export RAPIDAPI_KEY=your_actual_key
export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your_actual_key
export AFFINDA_API_TOKEN=your_actual_token

# Then start the application
java -jar target/backend-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar
```

## Testing API Keys

### Test RapidAPI
```bash
curl -X GET "https://jsearch.p.rapidapi.com/search?query=java+developer" \
  -H "X-RapidAPI-Key: YOUR_KEY" \
  -H "X-RapidAPI-Host: jsearch.p.rapidapi.com"
```

### Test OpenAI API
```bash
curl https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "gpt-3.5-turbo",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
  }'
```

## Security Notes

- ⚠️ NEVER commit .env file to Git
- ⚠️ Add .env to .gitignore
- ⚠️ Use different keys for dev/staging/production
- ⚠️ Rotate keys regularly
- ⚠️ Monitor API usage to stay within free tiers

## Cost Estimates (with Free Tiers)

- **RapidAPI JSearch**: FREE (5,000 requests/month)
- **OpenAI GPT-3.5**: ~$0.002 per 1K tokens ($5 free credit for new accounts)
- **Affinda Resume Parser**: FREE (100 resumes/month)
- **ipapi.co Geolocation**: FREE (1,000 requests/day)

Total monthly cost with free tiers: **$0** to **~$5-10** depending on usage
